## Plan: Complete 5e Mechanical Simulation

**TL;DR:** Build the game engine that makes the AI irrelevant to rule correctness. Six phases, each delivering a testable, self-contained mechanical system. When we're done, the AI is a narrator handed a completed turn — dice already rolled, damage already applied, conditions already checked. The server IS the dungeon master's math. The AI is just its voice.

**Current state:** 41 of 97 mechanical subsystems complete (42%). Types and data are rich. Runtime enforcement is skeletal. The engine trusts the AI for everything the rulebook should govern.

