### Implementation Order and Dependencies

```
Phase A (Core Rolls + Conditions) ─── no dependencies
   │
   ├──▶ Phase B (Combat Engine) ─── depends on A
   │       │
   │       └──▶ Phase C (Death, Conditions, Damage Types) ─── depends on A, B
   │
   ├──▶ Phase D (Spellcasting) ─── depends on A
   │
   ├──▶ Phase E (Rest & Recovery) ─── depends on A, D (spell slot recovery)
   │
   ├──▶ Phase F (Inventory & Equipment) ─── independent, but AC calc touches A
   │
   ├──▶ Phase G (Level Up) ─── depends on D (spell progression), F (proficiency recalc)
   │
   └──▶ Phase H (Travel & Environment) ─── largely independent
```

**Phases A, F, and H can start in parallel.** Phase B needs A. Phases C, D, E need A+B. Phase G needs D+F. This means the critical path is A → B → C (for combat completeness) and A → D → E (for resource management).

