### Decisions

- **Pure functions first, pipeline wiring later.** Every phase builds pure, testable game functions. Wiring them into the AI turn pipeline (the old Phase 4) happens AFTER the engine is complete.
- **No AI changes.** The AI prompt, context assembly, and response parsing stay untouched until the engine is done.
- **No UI changes.** No new Svelte components until the mechanics are solid. The game runs headless.
- **Multiclass is structural prep only.** Phase G adds the type-level support (`classes[]` instead of `class`). The full multiclass UI and selection flow remains in the original Phase 6.
- **Travel is simple.** Phase H uses fixed time heuristics and percentage-based random encounters. No hex grid, no pathfinding, no distance calculation. Good enough for a text RPG.
- **Critical path: A → D → E** (rolls → spells → rests) gives us the core 5e resource loop. Combat (B → C) can develop in parallel.

